Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Our\Nnext talk is improving your
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.16,0:00:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,relationships.\N>> Oh. Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.52,0:00:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. So, this can be um your\Nspiritual relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.92,0:00:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, improving relationships,\Nspiritualizing them to begin with
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.43,0:00:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,improves all of them. Oh,\N>> the awareness that that God is present
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.24,0:00:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,at all times\Nto be as loving as possible towards all
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.07,0:00:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of life and all of its expressions.\Num means to be kind to to to your
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.20,0:00:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,environment, to be kind to this couch,\Nto be kind to you, to be kind to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.39,0:00:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,be kind to my sweater, and not go and\Ntear it or rip it or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.68,0:00:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,not spill things on it.\NSo, I try to be as kind to my
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.48,0:00:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,environment as I can.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.03,0:01:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And invite and kind to other people's\Nenvironment. Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.32,0:01:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear an airplane coming overhead.\NYou hear them?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.84,0:01:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. We're just going to wait until it\Ngoes over.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.47,0:01:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> He's coming to torment us.\N>> Oh my goodness. If If that doesn't give
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.20,0:01:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you paranoia,\Nhow did that plane know that we didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.68,0:01:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,want the sound of an airplane in the\Nbackground?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.08,0:01:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, probably our dislike of the sound\Nof the air airplane in the background
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.96,0:01:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,attracted it.\N>> All right. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.72,0:01:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> great. Uh, all right. Um, all right. So,\Nimproving your relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.39,0:01:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Can you talk about u what one should\Nhave consideration for other people?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.43,0:02:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's a general rule of life.\NConsideration for life in all of its
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.52,0:02:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,expressions.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.60,0:02:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And of course, one of its major\Nexpressions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.67,0:02:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is the aliveness of the life of the\Npersons that are near you and you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.72,0:02:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,contribute to your life and to your\Nhappiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.56,0:02:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we try to be as loving as we can\Ntowards all of life in all of its
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.95,0:02:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,expressions\Nand especially those that are closest to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.28,0:02:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,us\Nand then they in turn pick up that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.36,0:02:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,energy and pass it on to others.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.44,0:02:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So when we're loving towards a friend\Nthey can they are therefore more loving
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.68,0:02:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,towards their friends and where are more\Nloving. So love you know like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.51,0:02:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,>> so it's kind of passed along.\N>> Yes. So lovingness I think to be as
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.23,0:02:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,loving as you can towards all of life\Nand all of its expressions all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.76,0:03:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is making a major contribution to life\Nto the overall energy of life
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.51,0:03:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and it creates a certain ambiance\Nthat affects everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.92,0:03:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as far as it goes, it says um re uh\Nyour relationship with God. Let's let's
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.64,0:03:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,cover that one first. Um\N>> wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.08,0:03:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Your relationship with God should be\Nwell on a daily, weekly, hourly basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.15,0:03:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Should be continuous.\N>> Could be continuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.87,0:03:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. that you're you you're aware that\Nyou are all constantly in the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.95,0:03:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of God\N>> and you pray to God whenever you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.00,0:03:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,remember that fact.\NSo I I ask God to help us speak as
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.12,0:03:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,fluently as we can at this moment in\Nwhatever manner might be most useful to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.92,0:03:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the listener or the viewer of this tape.\NMhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.36,0:04:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So part of God's love\Nthen expresses itself through me to the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.43,0:04:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,viewer and the listener.\N>> Um can you talk a little bit about um as
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.64,0:04:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual uh person\Num or
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.51,0:04:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirituality of one's life? Do you\Nturn your life over to God
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.07,0:04:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,uh when you know you know life is not\Nsmooth? So you turn your life over to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.19,0:04:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,God. Is that what you do?\NI I think the overall awareness that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.08,0:04:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,everything and all that you do is\Nconstantly in the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.08,0:04:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,already alters\Nyour way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.80,0:04:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I I think it tends to cancel\Nnegativities that you otherwise might
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.04,0:04:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,indulge in.\N>> On the other hand, God doesn't get upset
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.08,0:05:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,if you get mad at something.\N>> So in my view of God, God accepts human
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,limitation.\NAnd uh I was created by God and I was
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,created the way I am.\NAnd so instead of being unhappy or
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.12,0:05:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,cursing the way I am,\Nuh I thank God that I have such a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.24,0:05:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,versatility\Nof
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.84,0:05:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing the different aspects of\Nlife. I can experience angriness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.03,0:05:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,irritation and all those things and not\Nnot have it really interfere with my
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.56,0:05:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,real basic happiness which includes all\Nof those
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.72,0:05:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> as far as it goes. is repro improving\Nyour relationships. We have different
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,kinds of relationships. You know, we\Nhave a husband or a a partner
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.36,0:05:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship. We have a husband and wife\Nrelationship. We have, you know, child
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.32,0:05:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,uh parent relationships,\N>> siblings,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.60,0:06:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> siblings,\Nmother, father relationship. There's all
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.84,0:06:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,these different relationships.\NSo, can you tell us a little bit on how
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.24,0:06:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle uh juggle all these\Nrelationships
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.12,0:06:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,>> because with one you're this way and\Nwith one you're that way and it's just
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.47,0:06:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\N>> Yeah. We are we we we tend to alter our
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.24,0:06:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,behaviors\Nuh depending on the person that we're
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.60,0:06:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,with.\N>> Uh because some people are playful and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.52,0:06:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we can be playful with them. Other\Npeople are more serious, take everything
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.84,0:06:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,serious. other people you have to be\Nbusinesslike at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.00,0:06:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So people limit limit the way you can\Nrelate to them by the way they hold
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.68,0:06:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,themsself and present themsel.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.03,0:06:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Some I know some people that you have to\Nbe like businesslike with. You can't
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.80,0:06:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,really be jolly or joking or you can't\Ngive them a hug.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.91,0:06:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uhhuh. I wonder what would happen if you\Ngave him a hug and got scared. Well, I
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.56,0:07:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't think\N>> they probably would think it was
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.84,0:07:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,inappropriate.\N>> Yeah. There you go. Inappropriate. There
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.72,0:07:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you go.\N>> Inappropriate behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.16,0:07:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> There you go. There you go.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.08,0:07:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. So, on top of everything else, we\Nhave appropriateness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.63,0:07:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm. Not only the kind of person you are\Nin a given situation and setting
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.52,0:07:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but how you handle the whole range of\Nthat which could go from mild to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.63,0:07:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,considerable\Nuh intensity of expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.91,0:07:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's okay to be who you are\Nuh with limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.91,0:07:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um does God play an important part in\Nrelationships?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.12,0:07:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's the prevailing overall\Nattitude
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.91,0:07:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,um for many people\Nand other people are completely
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.40,0:07:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,oblivious.\NUh just ignore that God is present at
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.28,0:08:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,all times and it would put a damper on\Nwhat they can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.31,0:08:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It's hard to kill somebody if you're\Naware that you're doing this in the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.75,0:08:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\NHappily during the war I didn't have to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.28,0:08:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,kill anybody.\NI managed to uh steer the ship through
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.47,0:08:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,typhoons and keep us keep us alive while\Nother ships other ships I think 90 ships
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.47,0:08:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,sank in the Okanawa tycoon.\NAnd we went over to 90 actually 90
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.72,0:08:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,degrees. We were as horizontal as we\Nwere vertical.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.36,0:08:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I stayed at the wheel for I don't\Nknow close to two days without stopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.47,0:08:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,uh cuz I was not prone to seasickness. I\Nnever got seasick
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh and other people were laying on\Nthe on the deck very sick. I mean a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.16,0:08:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of them were very pathetically sick. I\Nreally felt sorry for him and I thank
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.04,0:09:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,God that I was not subject to uh to\Nseasickness and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so I was very thankful to be of service\Nand um
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.68,0:09:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,grateful for the opportunity to\Nbe of service to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.76,0:09:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Um can you um talk about\Num what I want to talk to you about is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.88,0:09:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,um how can one be loving when one's\Nfeelings are hurt
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.92,0:09:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to say a partner? How can one be loving\Nto the partner when their feelings are
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.27,0:09:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,hurt?\N>> Well, you mean you're the object or the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.95,0:09:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,subject?\N>> Well, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.00,0:09:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> somebody hurts your feelings.\N>> Feelings. Yeah. Okay. So, how can you be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.00,0:09:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,loving\N>> when Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.76,0:09:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> When somebody's hurt your feelings,\N>> right? You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.80,0:09:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> well, you can turn around and say the\Nmore people have hurt your feelings, the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.92,0:10:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,more loving you should be to try to\Novercome that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.39,0:10:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You want You know what I'm saying?\N>> So, if I'm being difficult right now
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.16,0:10:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh about understanding what you're\Nsaying,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.44,0:10:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I double my efforts to really understand\Nwhat what it is she's trying to say to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.92,0:10:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,me.\N>> Okay. what is it she really wants to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.39,0:10:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,bring out in the conversation.\NSo I'm I'm doubling my effort now to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.12,0:10:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehend\Nuh the point you would like me to make
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.04,0:10:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of the listener or the view\N>> viewer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.00,0:10:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So um so you should then you know\NI mean in the Bible it says turn the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.32,0:10:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,other cheek.\NSometimes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.88,0:10:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel like turning the other\Ncheek. So, what do you do then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.95,0:10:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I don't remember that that I tore that\Npage out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.48,0:10:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, okay.\N>> I threw that and threw that page away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.32,0:11:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What does that repeat? What does that\Nsays?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What is that teaching?\N>> Well, you know, it's like the meek shall
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.95,0:11:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,inherit the earth and turn the other\Ncheek. And you know, when you've been,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.60,0:11:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, insulted or hurt, you turn the\Nother cheek, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.80,0:11:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh. Be become non retaliatory.\N>> Non retaliatory. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.04,0:11:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And to just go with the flow.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.51,0:11:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uhhuh.\N>> That reminds me of a funny card. It says
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.51,0:11:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,only dead fish go with the flow.\N>> That's funny. That is funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.83,0:11:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nwould you say then that by turning the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.92,0:11:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,other cheek, say you've been insulted or\Nyour feelings are hurt, by turning the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.83,0:11:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,other cheek,\Ndoes that help promote a better
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.07,0:11:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship?\N>> It might and it might not. There's times
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.76,0:12:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn the other cheek is the wise\Nthing to do and there's other times when
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.64,0:12:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it is not the wise thing to do because\Nit'll invite more of the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.32,0:12:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\Nuh I think only up to a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.83,0:12:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,limitation,\N>> right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.68,0:12:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I turn the other cheek out of\Nconsideration for the other person's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.68,0:12:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,state of consciousness.\N>> I realize that they're doing the best
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.68,0:12:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they can.\NUh but if they could do better,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.80,0:12:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> uh I might expect them to do better by\Nsaying I'm I'm not going to go along
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.92,0:12:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with that. I understand what you mean by\Nit, but I'm not going to go along with
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.48,0:12:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\N>> Okay. I think that you could do better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.24,0:12:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um,\N>> you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.00,0:12:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> how important is it to be with\Nlike-minded people?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.48,0:12:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I think it's a matter of comfort to be\Nwith like-minded people
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.51,0:12:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because you don't have to explain\Nyourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.20,0:12:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, it just everything goes by\Npresumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.24,0:13:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> If you're not with like-minded people,\Nyou have to explain yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a foreign culture, I've lived in\Nforeign countries
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.00,0:13:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,where there is some degree of\Nexplanation, you really need
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.36,0:13:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,uh to explain yourself. So so they will\Nnot be offended.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.24,0:13:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the sake of their happiness,\NI would provide explanations that I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.16,0:13:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't ordinarily\Njust that so that they feel more
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.88,0:13:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,comfortable.\N>> Mhm. So you reach a certain point of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.92,0:13:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,life where the happiness of everybody\Naround you uh is important and you do
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.80,0:13:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what you can\Nwithin limitations
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.39,0:13:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,not to violate your own certain inner\Nexpectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.68,0:13:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want to violate your own code\Ninner code.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.95,0:13:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,>> If everybody's stealing something\Ndoesn't mean I'm going to join them
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.63,0:14:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> because I would experience guilt about\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.88,0:14:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain situations in life\Nwhere thievery becomes prevailing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.00,0:14:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> How can we have a deeper connection to\Nour higher self? Um, and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.92,0:14:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as that goes, um,\Nwould you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.16,0:14:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,bring the awareness of our higher self?\NSo, you just got done explaining, you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.88,0:14:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,know, that your principles um, you know,\Nif you everyone was stealing something
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.12,0:14:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that your principles would hold you back\Nbecause you would have guilt over over
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.48,0:14:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,stealing something. So\N>> um when your principles are being um
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.12,0:14:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,challenged that's when you would say\Ndon't turn the other cheek then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.92,0:14:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> There you go.\N>> Okay. So in your principles of who you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.76,0:15:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you know right and wrong or whatever uh\Nyour principles are um that would be the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.24,0:15:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,turning point as to not\N>> so you don't want to facilitate other
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,people's negativity.\N>> You know if they're all stealing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.48,0:15:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,something doesn't mean you have to join\Nthem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.27,0:15:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uhhuh. Mhm.\N>> Many of these things are so subtle and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.68,0:15:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so complicated\N>> that you can't really explain them in,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.63,0:15:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, because language is, you know,\Nlinear,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.16,0:15:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't explain a lot of things in\Nlinear logic. Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.95,0:15:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> There might be moments when joining the\Nfurry would be the thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> And
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.04,0:15:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,moments when the opposite would prevail.\NWould be wrong to join what prevails.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.32,0:15:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uhhuh.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.24,0:16:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So let's say during a typhoon, everybody\Nwas scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.75,0:16:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I'm not frightened\Nand everybody sees that I'm not
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.51,0:16:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,frightened, it could have what a couple\Nof different influences.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.51,0:16:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> It might throw them into shame over the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.95,0:16:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,fact that they're afraid and I'm not.\NOr it might encourage them that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.04,0:16:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,okay to exhibit your fear. Uh there's\Nnothing wrong with being scared to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.83,0:16:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,death. Mhm.\N>> There's times when it's very smart to be
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.95,0:16:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,scared.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.48,0:16:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So the fact that you let them know that\NI'm, you know, frankly I'm scared scared
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.75,0:16:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,lets it be okay for them to be scared.\N>> So when you were in that typhoon, did
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.83,0:16:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you have uh did you know that u God was\Nwith you? I mean did you know that that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.00,0:16:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,or\N>> and no in moments of high terror
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.24,0:17:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the conscious awareness of the\Npresence of God disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.72,0:17:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more like a prevailing condition\Nthat expresses itself less specifically
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.79,0:17:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> under certain circumstances.\NIt's a presumption. I don't think about
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.07,0:17:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of God all the time.\NIn fact, I seldom really think of it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.16,0:17:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,specifically.\N>> The fact that we are speaking right now
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.00,0:17:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in the presence of God is obviously a\Nfact.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.24,0:17:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But as we speak of it, I am not\Nconsciously aware of God being a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.76,0:17:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,witness, observer,\N>> participant, supervisor, prevailing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.88,0:17:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,condition.\NSo if a thing is a presumption of life
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.67,0:17:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then it doesn't have to be necessarily\Nrepeated. We could just assume that it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.96,0:17:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,prevails under all circumstances.\NWhat I'm saying to you now I hope will
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.84,0:18:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,be the best possible explanation I can\Nof answering your question.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.08,0:18:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,uh not for God's sake but for the sake\Nof the listener
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.64,0:18:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for the good good of all that it might\Nbe of help to someone to be more
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.16,0:18:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,accepting of human limitation.\NIt's okay to be scared and cowardly and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.67,0:18:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,fearful and regretful and it's okay to\Nhave negative feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.55,0:18:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,U and the thing is to not let them\Ndominate your life
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.12,0:18:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> to accept them as a passing phenomena\Nand often a necessary one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.88,0:18:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean just as they're going to put you\Nto sleep to do surgery on you naturally
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.32,0:18:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to feel natural feel fear.\NYou hope that everything goes all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.96,0:18:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't cut off the wrong ear.\NOh, this year you cut the wrong ear off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.03,0:19:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Does um would you say in a in a partner\Nrelationship um does love hold you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.52,0:19:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,together?\N>> Does it is it the love for each other
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.48,0:19:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that holds you together or is it the\Nlove of who that person is? What really
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.76,0:19:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,holds you together in a in a loving\Nrelationship? I think that that specific
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.84,0:19:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,energy\Nlove is both specific and non-specific.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.52,0:19:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But in a specific uh relationship, the\Nspecifics become very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.36,0:19:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we love those who we love because\Nwe're a loving person to begin with. In
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.28,0:19:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,addition to which\Nwe we learn to love many of their
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.52,0:19:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristics.\NI know for instance that you will always
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.36,0:19:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,do the best possible j job you can about\Nanything that you do because that's just
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.00,0:19:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who you are and it's okay that at times\Nyou don't you say no it's too much
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:20:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,bother to make breakfast this morning\Nwe'll do without it today
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.00,0:20:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so then you say we're not having bacon\Nand eggs this morning okay
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.03,0:20:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,if we are it's terrific and if or not,\Nit's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.24,0:20:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> So, but um the love that you have for
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.08,0:20:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,each other, does that hold you together\Nor is it just
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.40,0:20:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,another aspect of\N>> Well, you are together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.79,0:20:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I I I feel it holds us together. Yeah. I\Nfeel
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.55,0:20:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I feel that it holds us together.\NSo in other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.91,0:20:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> yeah, is a generality.\N>> You have to love yourself before someone
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.44,0:20:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,else can love you. Is that what you're\Nsaying?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.55,0:20:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, that's a nice way of putting it. I\Ndon't know necessarily true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.48,0:20:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> You cannot love yourself too much and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.36,0:21:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,love other people a lot. I think\Nuh or vice versa. love yourself and not
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.96,0:21:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,love many people.\NSo, it's a variable quality
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.28,0:21:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think different circumstances\Nbring it forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.28,0:21:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> There's that airplane that loves us. You
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.60,0:21:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,hear it comes over us.\N>> Yes, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.84,0:21:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It keeps flying over us to say, "Oh, I\Nlove you down there. You're talking and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.44,0:21:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't want me to make noise, but I\Nlove you so much. I'm going to make some
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.24,0:21:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,noise so you can say how much you love\Nme even though I'm making noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.67,0:21:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\N>> so you're saying that uh in uh the love
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.32,0:21:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for each other that you hold, the love\Nthat you have for each other as a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.00,0:21:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,um that\Nwould you say that um similar goals as
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.67,0:22:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,far as it goes as your spirituality is\Nimportant as well as um
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.52,0:22:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,your relationship with each other.\N>> Well, if you call love spiritual to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.64,0:22:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,begin with, you know, then then it it\Nprevails all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.12,0:22:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> Uh if you call it just an emotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.15,0:22:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,then that's a different thing.\NBut love is both an emotion and a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.24,0:22:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual condition. In my my experience\Nof it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.55,0:22:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,um the willingness, the capacity to be\Nloving
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.03,0:22:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is already a spiritual\Ncondition that prevails.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.79,0:22:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people tend to be loving uh at all\Ntimes and in all places
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.76,0:22:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> with few exceptions.\NTakes a lot to make them stop being
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.24,0:22:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,loving.\N>> All right. um if someone was in say a a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.08,0:22:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,bad relationship or quote toxic u\Nrelationship
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.03,0:23:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nyou know is that in their mind is tox
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.55,0:23:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,toxic or is it in you know I mean you\Nyou always ask yourself that how can I
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.96,0:23:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what am I doing wrong in this\Nrelationship you know how can I make
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.12,0:23:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,this relationship better especially if\Nyou've been with someone for quite a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.32,0:23:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it just that you ignored those\Nuh behaviors?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.08,0:23:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, I think that one's one's capacity\Nto uh comprehend limitation varies
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.88,0:23:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on many local conditions.\N>> Okay. uh your willingness for instance
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.36,0:23:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,um and then every relationship goes\Nthrough periods of ups and downs I think
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.40,0:23:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and periods when the other person is\Npreoccupied with other demands
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.15,0:24:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,uh in our relationship I'm very aware\Nuh of timing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.79,0:24:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because if my timing is wrong and you're\Nunder stress
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.28,0:24:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,uh from other demands in your life, I\Nknow you won't have the the time or the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.64,0:24:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,energy or the tolerance for for an\Nadditional one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.44,0:24:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, consideration, part of love is\Nconsideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.24,0:24:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh knowing what kind of the situation\Nthe other person is in,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.36,0:24:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, as far as stress, family,\Nrelationships, physical health, and many
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.52,0:24:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,other things, many other factors.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.76,0:24:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you you're under a lot of\Ndemands by a lot of people, which you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.27,0:24:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,often are, I try to make my request to\Nyou as limited as possible because I
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.60,0:24:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,realize you're already under stress.\NYou know, multiple family members,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.91,0:24:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,friends, neighbors, God knows what all\N>> and uh so I try to keep my own
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.88,0:25:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,expectation down to\Nmore appropriate time and location. Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.08,0:25:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So we try to time our expectations.\N>> Well, we know that um in one's
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.32,0:25:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship with other people, it's\Nvery difficult to you know be totally
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.79,0:25:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> emerged in that relationship at all\Ntimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.24,0:25:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It's not even very healthy to be that\Nway really.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.20,0:25:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um you know, so you do some things apart\Nand some things together.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.91,0:25:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. you know\N>> and that adds to the enjoyment.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.03,0:25:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> So some things you enjoy being with
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.88,0:25:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody\Nand other other people other things you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.27,0:25:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoy being apart.\NSo that adds to the flavor. It's like
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.91,0:25:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the weather being different different\Ndays of the week.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.60,0:25:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You know, a rainy day would not be happy\Nevery day,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.03,0:25:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> but once in a great while it's sort of\Nfun. and all of a sudden it's raining
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.88,0:26:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,out and it's exciting.\NI think there's a there's one roof where
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.27,0:26:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we live where you can really hear the\Nrain and I always get a kick out of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.88,0:26:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,going on that room and you can hear it\Npeling down on the roof and Wow, listen
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.03,0:26:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to that.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.40,0:26:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I always know when it snows because you\Ncan't hear it when it hits. It just kind
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.27,0:26:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of drifts and so you come out and all of\Na sudden everything's white.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.79,0:26:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The rain you can hear, but the snow it\Nalways comes down very softly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.27,0:26:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You never know it's there until you get\Nup.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.96,0:26:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, I grew up in Wisconsin and more\Nsnow was not exactly an exciting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.88,0:26:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,development for the morning. In Arizona,\Nsnow is exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.88,0:26:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah, it is.\N>> So many of the things then depend on the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.72,0:26:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,circumstances.\NSnow in Wisconsin was not an exciting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.60,0:26:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,development. Snow in Arizona. Wow.\NEverybody gets up and runs to the window
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.64,0:26:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and says, "Look, there's snow."\N>> That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.27,0:26:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Very exciting.\N>> They do the same with rain, too, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.20,0:27:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> For what?\N>> Rain. They do the same with rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.15,0:27:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh,\N>> yeah. Another rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.96,0:27:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I think more people go out in the rain\Nin Arizona than stay in.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.44,0:27:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nso when we get back to relationships and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.64,0:27:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,would you say that um a relationship\Nthat has a spiritual base is stronger
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.76,0:27:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,than say one that does not.\N>> I I think it isn't that um the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.27,0:27:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,base means accountability.\N>> Accountability of what? Accountability
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.96,0:27:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of one's overall condition of\Nlovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.52,0:27:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So a non-spiritual relationship allows\Npeople to do things that uh uh spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.55,0:27:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,people would never consider doing.\NHurting other people's feelings in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.67,0:27:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,certain ways for instance selling them\Nor
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.27,0:27:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> uh\N>> or physical violence or whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.52,0:28:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> cruelty of any kind you know and if you\Nmake a mistake you apologize for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.84,0:28:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\NSo, for instance, if I if I'm being
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.84,0:28:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,dumb, you know, I apologize for being\Ndumb and I'll say, "Geez, that was a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.27,0:28:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,dumb thing to say or a dumb thing to\Ndo." Or
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.03,0:28:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that would dumb.\N>> So, um, would you say that knowing when
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.96,0:28:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to say gosh, I'm sorry, is a very\Nimportant part of a relationship?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.79,0:28:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I I think that really helps really helps\Na lot. the willingness to say uh
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.44,0:28:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,uh I was mistaken. I'm sorry that I\Ncomplained
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.32,0:28:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and um\Nso cordiality that that's part of being
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.39,0:28:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,cordial.\N>> So loving relationship is also one
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.96,0:28:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that's cordial.\NCordial means a consideration for the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.64,0:28:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,feelings of others\N>> to express things in a way that is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.44,0:29:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uplifting rather than downgrading.\N>> So would you say that you would put
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.76,0:29:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,someone else's feelings ahead of your\Nown or would you say you would just con
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.60,0:29:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you should consider the other person's\Nfeelings?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.27,0:29:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You would consider it and sometimes you\Nwould put the other person's feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.96,0:29:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,ahead of your own. Uh other times, uh\Nthey could wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.32,0:29:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> Uh you can wait till you get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.03,0:29:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to express everything\Nwhile you're in the middle of the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.48,0:29:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,highway.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.67,0:29:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You know, and then when you get home,\Nyou can say, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.72,0:29:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you shouldn't have passed him on the\Nright.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.79,0:29:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm. Mhm.\N>> If you don't want to say it at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.91,0:29:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> So many of these things have to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.20,0:29:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,timing. Mhm.\N>> And the subtlety
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.67,0:29:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and the totality of the overall\Nuh set of conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.91,0:30:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> But we all uh could improve in some way
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.64,0:30:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in some area. So it's it's fun when\Nyou're bored. You can sit down and say
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.44,0:30:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,now in what way could I improve myself\N>> and under what conditions could I
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.60,0:30:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,improve myself?\NSo if we took like a uh an inventory
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.32,0:30:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> there, there you go.\N>> So you take a personal inventory,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.76,0:30:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> a moral inventory, right? They do that\Nin the 12step group. You take
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.60,0:30:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,periodically you take a moral inventory\N>> and uh ask God to point out where you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.36,0:30:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,could improve and ask for help to\Nimprove in that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.36,0:30:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You could be more considerate of others.\NYou could be less selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.96,0:30:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I know. That's something people don't\Ntake the time to do
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.72,0:30:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> is to\N>> uh
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.79,0:30:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> well if a spiritually oriented person\Ndoes take time to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.79,0:31:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,um you do take time to do a periodic\Nmoral inventory
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.79,0:31:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> you know where could I improve myself\N>> in 12 12steps group you do that every
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.08,0:31:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,day every day you ask for knowledge of\NGod's will for you and the power to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.36,0:31:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,carry it out I ask for God ask for\Nknowledge of God's will for me and the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.15,0:31:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,power to carry that out. In other words,\Nand then you're asking divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.64,0:31:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,um to point out to you where you would\Nbe of greater service to God to man your
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.84,0:31:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,fellow human being and also of course to\Nyour own self.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.39,0:31:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so it might be more kind, more\Nthoughtful, might be
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.60,0:31:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,um or it might be the opposite way to\Nstop being so selfacing and speak up for
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.55,0:31:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself periodically.\N>> It just depends on the individual
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.12,0:31:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and the circumstances which in human\Nlife can be quite complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.20,0:32:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we were to sum this up kind of\Nit's you should have some kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.79,0:32:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual base for a strong\Nrelationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.88,0:32:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I think of a spiritual orientation by\Nboth people gives much greater strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.03,0:32:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N>> Right. And you should have consideration
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.39,0:32:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and timing for the other person\Nwhen approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.00,0:32:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of lovingness is right\N>> being considerate of their mood and what
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.00,0:32:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,other pressures are prevailing on their\Nlife and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.12,0:32:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> what time demand is on them\N>> and um
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.51,0:32:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,uh what was the other one I was going to\Nsay? Oh, and taking a moral inventory of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.15,0:32:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself\N>> periodically. A moral inventory.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.39,0:32:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I think of course going to church serves\Nthat for some people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.96,0:32:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes, it does. I mean on Sunday they do a\Nmoral eliminatory when they go to church
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.12,0:32:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,period.\N>> Other people it's a way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.60,0:33:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people it's constant to always be\Naware where you could be doing a better
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.55,0:33:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,job.\N>> Like right now I could be doing maybe a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.24,0:33:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,better job of explaining\Nmy answers to your questions. So as I
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.27,0:33:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,answer it, I am also sort of like\Nfeeling within myself how I could become
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.91,0:33:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,more fluent, how I could be more fluent\Nand express uh in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.96,0:33:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,more explicitly\Nthe answer I would like to deliver to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.44,0:33:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.36,0:33:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So relationships\Nwe will always have to deal with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.76,0:33:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh whether it's um a partnership a\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.96,0:33:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> God\N>> God
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.55,0:33:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> mankind\N>> children
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.36,0:33:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> accountability\N>> accountability we haven't touched on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.64,0:34:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,accountability\N>> no because it scares people the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.12,0:34:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that you know you're accountable for\Nyour actions
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.96,0:34:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and of course that's one reason people\Nare scared to death of dying is they're
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.91,0:34:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't want to be accountable able\Nand to God for their shortcomings and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.39,0:34:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,their limitations and their sins and\Nof commission and omission.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.24,0:34:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,God, how can I explain that I did not\Nspend more time
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.32,0:34:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,being considerate of others instead of\Ncons of being selfishly preoccupied with
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.11,0:34:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,my own self and my own possessions, my\Nown pleasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.15,0:34:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people play golf. Other people go\Nto church on Sunday morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.63,0:34:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Is one better than the other? No. You\Ncould do a bad job of going to church
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.56,0:34:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and a great job of great job of being\Nloving and friendly playing golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.80,0:34:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> So you can't always tell by the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.00,0:35:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,impertinances. Mhm.\N>> So if so we have to when we do that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.96,0:35:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,moral inventory then we have to at least\Naddress being accountable for our acts
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.35,0:35:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> that you're willing to take\Nresponsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.64,0:35:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,>> that it was you that yes and said it and\Ndid it and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.35,0:35:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't have to be hard on\Nyourself. In other words, it doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.04,0:35:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,mean to be tough on yourself.\N>> You can realize that at the time you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.68,0:35:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,were working under limitations\Nand you did the best you could under
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.64,0:35:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,those limitations.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.96,0:35:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Had you had better conditions, you could\Nhave done a better job. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.64,0:35:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in theory at least, we all could be\Ndoing a little bit better than we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.72,0:35:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I could be speaking more clearly than I\Nam possibly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.92,0:36:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But not likely\Nbecause my intention when I speak is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.80,0:36:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,always to be as clear\N>> uh as as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.80,0:36:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of the listener\Nand uh for the sake of myself that I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.68,0:36:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm being understood in what I'm saying.\Nhere. Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.48,0:36:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Do you think that um well, you know, men\Nare from Mars, women are from Venus?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.83,0:36:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a great book because it points\Nout they just address things
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.04,0:36:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,differently. You address, you know, a\Nwoman would address it from this angle
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.96,0:36:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and a man addresses it from this angle.\N>> Yeah. You know, and once you read that,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.44,0:36:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand how why thing they just\Nthink differently, you know, when
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.24,0:36:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,handling problems, you know, and I\Nnoticed that with you. You you are
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.88,0:37:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,always very concerned about solving the\Nproblem. Now, what is the problem? You
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.16,0:37:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,know, you always say to me, now what is\Nthe problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.80,0:37:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You know, after I've emotionalized on\Nit,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.64,0:37:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> you always say, now what exactly is the\Nproblem?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.20,0:37:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Is that what I do?\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.00,0:37:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, then I have to stop and\Nthink, well, yeah, I did emotionalize on
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.40,0:37:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it and I have to present you to with the\Nproblem that I'm trying to solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.40,0:37:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What is the problem?\N>> Yeah. What is the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.48,0:37:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I do that.\N>> Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.56,0:37:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh,\N>> you make me go back instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.92,0:37:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalizing about it.\N>> Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.16,0:37:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You make me\N>> look at the under problem at the real,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.59,0:37:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, what exactly is it that's\Nbothering
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.07,0:37:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I'm a fragmentist, right? Yeah. Well,\Nyou I mean I think it's just a man
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.88,0:37:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,thing. I don't think it's anything that\Nyou are. I just think it's the way a man
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.24,0:37:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,looks at things that come up in life.\N>> Could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.68,0:37:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Yeah. Pragmatically. Yeah. So the the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.52,0:37:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,man is more pragmatic is\N>> uh although when in other conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.28,0:38:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,though it's the woman is more pragmatic\N>> sometimes
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.16,0:38:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> when it comes to healing people's\Nfeelings especially those of children
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.20,0:38:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and people around them.\NUm to that to the woman, the most
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.80,0:38:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,practical thing is to calm everybody\Ndown and make them feel better.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.76,0:38:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The guys thinking they can take care of\Ntheir own
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.28,0:38:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,feelings.\N>> That's true, too. But um it just seems
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.40,0:38:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,like re all relationships are very\Ncomplicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.64,0:38:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> They really are when you examine them.\Nwhen you really look at them and examine
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.56,0:38:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,them, no matter what kind of\Nrelationship it is, it's very compliment
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.88,0:38:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,complicated with all these different\Naspects and then you add emotion to that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.35,0:38:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't see how anything ever gets\Nhealed or solved or you know fixed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.92,0:38:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know after how do they get you know\Nhow do you even come to a conclusion on
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.64,0:38:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,this? Well, because there's enough\Ntolerance. There's enough cushioning in
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.20,0:39:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,life.\NNo, we want to be polite to the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.72,0:39:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,policeman.\N>> Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.92,0:39:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,he says, "You got to wait for the red\Nlight." And so you uh try to be polite
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.20,0:39:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to the policeman. You wait for the red\Nlight, but you might be in a hurry and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.83,0:39:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "The heck with the policeman. I'm\Ngoing to cross against the red light
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.28,0:39:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,whether he likes it or not."\NSo the conditions that prevail dominate
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.20,0:39:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,all the decisions and how you feel about\Nthem.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.32,0:39:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay?\N>> It might be there might be times when
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.04,0:39:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's wrong uh to do exactly what the\Npoliceman thinks you should be doing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.68,0:39:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because he doesn't know the other\Nconditions that you have to face when
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.72,0:39:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to the other side of the street.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.48,0:39:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So at times we have to take charge\Nof our own situation
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.04,0:39:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever the consequences might be.\NAnd the willingness to accept the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.11,0:40:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,consequences of those variations\Nuh are what add to our the strength of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.83,0:40:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,our adulthood. You might say\Nif I look at myself as capable of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.52,0:40:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,handling many different situations\Nand different conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.35,0:40:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then um I'll feel better about myself\Nand and I'll be more willing to take
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.48,0:40:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,chances.\NSo it would make me more capable as a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.04,0:40:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,person than one who's more limited and\Nintolerant. Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.07,0:40:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I got mad yesterday about something.\NUh oh yes, I remember. I got mad that I
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.59,0:40:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't see the way I used to see.\NWell, I went blind in one eye and poor
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.96,0:40:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,poor vision one eye and blind in the\Nother
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.32,0:40:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for some reason. I've gotten used to\Nthat. For some reason, I suddenly got
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.16,0:40:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,mad about it\Nand uh I did something stupid. But I
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.44,0:41:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't see very well. And so I got mad\Nand threw my clothes on the on the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.56,0:41:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,floor.\NDidn't I Is that what I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.59,0:41:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah, that's what you did.\N>> I think I did. I I said, "I can't see
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.64,0:41:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the damn thing." And I threw the clothes\Non the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.07,0:41:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, that's more frustration than it\Nwas anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.40,0:41:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah,\Nthat's the inner child, right? The inner
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.16,0:41:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,child.\N>> Yeah. I got mad at myself. I got mad at
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.20,0:41:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,not being able to see. And so I threw my\Nclothes on the floor. I think it was
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.04,0:41:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,funny. And as soon as I did it, I said,\N"Was that good or bad?" Well, depends on
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.44,0:41:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,how you look at it.\N>> I didn't pick them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.20,0:41:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, I thought it was good that I I\Nsuppress my emotions most of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.35,0:41:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that I I feel are unsocial,\Nnot socially acceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.56,0:41:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordinarily, I would repress being angry\Nover limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.88,0:42:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, but for some reason I was freer with\Nmyself. I said, "The hell with it." And
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.59,0:42:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I took my clothes and I threw them on\Nthe floor and I was mad that I can't see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.11,0:42:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out of my right eye anymore.\N>> I was mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.96,0:42:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Mad that I can't see like I wish I could
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.59,0:42:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,see or I used to see.\NThen I let it be okay to be mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.56,0:42:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> Yeah. So then I then I had to give up
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.07,0:42:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling guilty that I was mad.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.24,0:42:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Then I felt good I was mad. I said,\N"Well, thank God you felt mad about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.20,0:42:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Express your being mad about it.\NAt least you're being emotionally
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.88,0:42:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,honest." And\N>> but see, those are things that come up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.80,0:42:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you with the physical, too.\NYou know, you never know. Um, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.64,0:42:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,people can be very um short with you and\Nyou don't know if something's going on
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.40,0:42:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,physically with that person.\N>> Yes, that's true. or you know they just
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.72,0:42:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,were told bad news. You never know. So\Nyou know a lot of people go well they
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.76,0:43:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,weren't very nice to me\N>> you know so
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.16,0:43:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> you know\Nyou have to take all those things into
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.04,0:43:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,consideration too\N>> right? So it's best to be as tolerant as
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.96,0:43:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be under the circumstances.\NOf course the downside of that is people
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.56,0:43:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,consider you're wishywashy and they can\Nwalk all over you and abuse you. So it's
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.28,0:43:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a so everything that we say there's a\Nlimitation. There's a top side to it and
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.59,0:43:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a downside to it.\N>> There is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.07,0:43:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> uh it's not they're not we're not\Ndealing with
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.80,0:43:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> it's not clear. We're not dealing with\Nclear things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.24,0:43:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,>> When you when you come with human\Nemotions, you're never dealing with
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.35,0:43:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutes.\N>> You're always dealing with relatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.92,0:43:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And depends on circumstances and timing\Nand your age at the time and how old you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.80,0:43:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,were and what your physical, mental and\Nfinancial condition was.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.16,0:43:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it wrong to spend this much money for\Nsomething or other? Depends on your
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.20,0:44:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,overall financial condition.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.07,0:44:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And that of your family and\Nyour obligation to society and your
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.96,0:44:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,culture etc. Mhm.\N>> Everything is really far more
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.31,0:44:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,complicated on the one hand, far more\Ncomplicated than it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.56,0:44:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh and far more difficult than it seems.\NOn the other hand, alternately
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.83,0:44:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,paradoxically,\Nuh things are also quite simple and not
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.56,0:44:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as complicated as as they seem.\N>> So I just took the clothes and I said
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.48,0:44:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the heck of them and threw them on the\Nfloor.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.64,0:44:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That was simple enough.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.28,0:44:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And then I feel guilty about that. So I\Npicked them up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.72,0:44:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> But at least you got your frustration\Nout.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.88,0:44:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. Right. Yeah. Yeah. It was fun.\N>> It was fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.44,0:45:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I mean, I seldom indulge myself that\Nway, you know? It's like,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.40,0:45:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I know.\N>> I couldn't throw your clothes on the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.48,0:45:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,floor. I mean, it's like unheard of.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.16,0:45:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,show you might say was it pleasing my\Ninner child.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.83,0:45:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, so out of all of this we should take\Nuh we should try be considerate of other
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.88,0:45:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,people.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.52,0:45:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> At all times try and take a moral\Ninventory on how you can either see it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.04,0:45:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,differently or to improve on oneself.\NAnd these things can all go on sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.80,0:45:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically,\N>> right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.56,0:45:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uh semiconsciously without necessarily\Nexclusively focusing on them in a formal
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.28,0:45:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,way,\N>> but always aware that you're accountable
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.64,0:45:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for your maturity of your responses and\Nyour emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.56,0:45:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You should respect the other person's\Nfeelings and situations they may be in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.83,0:46:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\NAnd I believe in being as tolerant as
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.52,0:46:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you can of other people's limitations.\NI think being a human human being is a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.28,0:46:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,very difficult\N>> very is frankly quite difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.59,0:46:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,uh we may not think so we've gotten in\Nnerd to it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.35,0:46:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> because we're used to it but it's\Nfrankly quite difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.31,0:46:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,being a human being very often\N>> and um being consideration having a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.92,0:46:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,consideration for um\Nsituations
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.31,0:46:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,um\NI think being sympathetic to other
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.20,0:46:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,people's\Nconditions of other people's lives and
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.80,0:46:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,their limitations.\NDon't you think so? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.04,0:46:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Makes you compassion.\N>> Yeah. to a compassionate human being is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.11,0:46:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,aware of the limitations of being human\Nuh in general and then specifically in
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.11,0:47:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,certain circumstances\N>> to be more forgiving than usual and more
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.24,0:47:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,loving than usual\N>> and then re respecting uh the other
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.07,0:47:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,person's you know space basically and\Ntheir and their um complicated life as
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.04,0:47:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,well as your own. So you know we have a\Ntendency to only look at ourselves and
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.28,0:47:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,say I I want you know I can't handle\Nthis. Yeah. Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.31,0:47:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you consider the conditions that\Nother people infect other living beings,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.83,0:47:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,not only people,\N>> but even your pets and your animals? And
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.44,0:47:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> how many days can your canary go without\Nbeing fed and have new water and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.40,0:47:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> right?\N>> How many hours can you be gone and your
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.04,0:47:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doggy, you know, start to miss you\Nbadly? And you got to really try to make
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.24,0:47:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,your doggy feel better when you get\Nhome.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.16,0:47:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\Nmake it. There's nothing makes you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.72,0:47:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,happier than a dog's waggy tail.\N>> That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.52,0:48:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, I like to think of other people in\Nthose terms. I like to see other
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.92,0:48:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,people's tails wagging.\N>> I like it when you're wagging your tail
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.20,0:48:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and you you think\N>> Thanks, Nate.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.64,0:48:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's not everybody that gets\Ncalled a dog. if you if you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.64,0:48:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I mean that's the waggginess\N>> is a quality of of feeling feeling life
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.92,0:48:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and making it\N>> and u wagggininess is is something we
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.83,0:48:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,like to bring forth in others. You know\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.55,0:48:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> other people will enjoy our presence and\Nwe're doing what we can to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.48,0:48:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> butter their toast on one side instead\Nof both sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.80,0:48:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, so relationships are, you know,\Nthey can be good, they can be bad. Um
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.35,0:49:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's is it some of it is what we make it\N>> a good deal of it certainly what we make
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.40,0:49:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it\N>> okay
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.48,0:49:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> consciously but as I said that\N>> that varies from condition to condition
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.04,0:49:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because some some things are just\N>> you've decided on a certain lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.92,0:49:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> that automatically has consequences.\N>> Okay. Then you've decided on you've
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.55,0:49:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,settled for certain human attitudes\Nuh as habits of ways of being in ways of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.59,0:49:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,being a human being\N>> and they have consequences too. So
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.88,0:49:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we it's it's a many many uh multifaceted\Nand complex situation
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.76,0:49:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,how you decide you want to be as a human\Nbeing in this life.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.64,0:49:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to be lovable and and loved.\N>> Um or you want to be completely
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.48,0:49:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,self-centered and disputatious.\NSo, we make these decisions all the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.00,0:50:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,time.\NYou could be disputatious in the morning
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.52,0:50:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and then decide that's that's horrible\Nand lunchtime change to being friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.04,0:50:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I think being a human being is very\Ncomplex.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.96,0:50:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a wonder that anyone has a\Nrelationship that works with all these
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.04,0:50:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,blocks that\N>> all things that could go wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.35,0:50:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> could go wrong.\N>> Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.31,0:50:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. It's very difficult.\N>> The other thing is say if we could be
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.68,0:50:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,better we would be.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.55,0:50:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That could be is the hypothetical.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.07,0:50:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> In reality you can only be as friendly\Nas you're capable of being that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.31,0:50:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Some days you're capable more capable of\Nbeing friendly than other days. you're
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.88,0:50:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,not really capable\Nbecause you have other human conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.64,0:50:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that prevail,\N>> right?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.64,0:50:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And all these conditions, you know,\Ndominate brain chemistry.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.28,0:50:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So all this doesn't happen in a vacuum.\NWhat you're talking about is human
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.00,0:51:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,hormones\Nand emotions and the biochemical
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.76,0:51:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,physiologic reactions thereof.\NAll of which have very uh strong
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.44,0:51:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,consequences, very serious ones.\N>> So what words of wisdom can you give us
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.59,0:51:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,about relationships\N>> to be God or
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.24,0:51:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I think to be as loving as possible\Nand to be aware in the back of your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.92,0:51:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're accountable.\NI'm always aware that I'm incountable
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.72,0:51:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for one thing to myself\Nspeak as fluently as I would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.52,0:51:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,have spoken but I'm also aware that all\Nthis is not happening in a vac in a
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.64,0:51:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,vacuum that there is an ultimate\Naccountability to divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.48,0:51:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill my potentiality to the best\Nof my ability
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.88,0:52:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,not only for myself but for the people\Naround and the world around me
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.07,0:52:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> to make life as pleasant as I can. So if\NI'm in a store, I want to make the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.59,0:52:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,encounter with the clerk behind the\Ncounter as pleasant as possible for the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.55,0:52:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,clerk\Nto be a pleasant customer instead of a
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.83,0:52:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,complaining obnoxious one.\NSome people don't seem to mind being
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.04,0:52:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,obnoxious\Nand uh they always sort of amaze me, but
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.24,0:52:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,they do. They don't care how nasty or\Ndemanding they are or vulgar or loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.11,0:52:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh I always say to myself, now how\Nare people like that brought up?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.92,0:52:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Who brought them up or failed to bring\Nthem up rather?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.31,0:52:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in being as loving in as you\Ncan in all conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.28,0:52:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to be as loving to the clerk behind the\Ncounter as you are to the cop on the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.59,0:53:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,beat to your family and your grandmother\Non the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.28,0:53:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Be as loving as you can towards all of\Nlife. To the doggy on the corner and to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.64,0:53:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the kitty that's lost and is hungry and\Nwants some milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.83,0:53:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say kitty kitty kitty. This morning\NI did.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.35,0:53:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> They all line up.\N>> I did. I said, "Kitty, kitty, kitty."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.28,0:53:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, all the kitties lined up.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.44,0:53:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> so um relationships\Num we have good ones, we have bad ones
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.00,0:53:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh in the end uh a relationship that\Nis centered around God
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.72,0:53:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,um kind of keeps us in check.\N>> I I think it brings it back to reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.35,0:54:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. that no matter how how how you\Nmuch you want to excuse it that that uh
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.64,0:54:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still accountable to to get to\NGod in the end that you did the best you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.76,0:54:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,could under the circumstances.\NIf you could have done better, you would
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.16,0:54:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.48,0:54:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I'm I'm always aware that we are always\Nin the presence of God at all times and
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.31,0:54:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,accountable to God.\NAlso, God in a way is like a giant
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.44,0:54:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,recording machine. Everything you've\Never said or done is registered somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.00,0:54:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in in the reality of divinity.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.04,0:54:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Forever.\NSo there's a to me it is there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.40,0:54:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,certain permanence to divinity\N>> that uh a thing you have done or said is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.83,0:54:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a permanent imprint\Ndoesn't mean the consequences are
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.00,0:54:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,permanent but the happening the event\Nand how it was handled the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.11,0:55:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> is a is a permanent imprint that's there\Nhistorically.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.40,0:55:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mhm.\NSo you might say each of us represents a
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.72,0:55:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,collection of our own personal history\Nfrom moment to moment
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.68,0:55:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and that personal history is variable\Nfrom moment to moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.64,0:55:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So right as I speak now I'm either\Nmaking it better or worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.16,0:55:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh by trying to be flexible,\NI try to create an atmosphere that the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.28,0:55:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,listener is as forgiving and gentle with\Nthemsel as I'm trying to be in a general
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.44,0:55:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,way.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.04,0:55:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That we all make, you know, errors that\Nwe wish we had not made. That that's
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.31,0:55:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,part of the human condition. It's okay\Nto love oursel
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.83,0:55:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,>> even though we've made mistakes.\NAnd also part of our loving ourself is
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.35,0:56:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to avoid him in the future you\Nknow for sake of pleasantness of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.31,0:56:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,existence for the sake of the welfare of\Nothers. So the happier we are as a human
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.83,0:56:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,being more satisfied we are the more\Nbeneficial we are to other humans. So
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.20,0:56:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you're being good good to other people\Nwhen you're good to yourself because
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.04,0:56:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're becoming a more pleasant and\Npositive human being to be around. So
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.76,0:56:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're adding to the pool of human\Nexperience is something that's positive
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.64,0:56:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of something that's negative. So\NI believe in being as happy and positive
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.35,0:56:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as you can at all times under all\Ncircumstances for the good and the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.92,0:56:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,welfare of everything and everyone\Nas well as
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.76,0:56:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,uh gratitude to God for one's existence.\NOne way to express gratitude is to be
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.55,0:56:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the best, most loving, generous,\Ncapable,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.68,0:56:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasing human being that you can be.\NMhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.79,0:57:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. Thank you, honey.\N>> Thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.07,0:57:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah.\NHallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.28,0:57:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah.\NHallelujah.
